@jeanlf, looks like everything is ok now, but perhaps one thing can be improved.

Right now, the default mode is the "inband". That's ok if codecs are different, but perhaps it's not really a good choice if codecs are the same, since looks like web-browsers or media players don't really support "avc3.*" media very well. I guess, it would be better if MP4Box would look at codecs in all Representations, and, based on this information, it would choose the mode to use (if the mode wasn't explicitly specified). For example, if all Representations use the same codec - the mode is "no". If codecs are different - the mode is "inband".

I'm just thinking about how people will be creating DASH media. Previously they didn't have to think about bitstream switching at all. Now, suddenly, they will start getting "avc3.*" instead of "avc1.*", which will result in https://github.com/Dash-Industry-Forum/dash.js/issues/445.

